jrobots.simulation.simulationObjects.collision

Class MotionTargetLaunchable

  • java.lang.Object
    • jrobots.simulation.simulationObjects.collision.MotionTargetLaunchable

  • public class MotionTargetLaunchable
extends java.lang.Object
    MotionTargetProjectile is used as a preliminary end point of a Launchable's move. The reason for this is about collision.

    in this momentary implementation the starting point of the movement is also included in order to detach some collision routines from the originating Launchable, called inceptor. A linear projectile movement is assumed, that is why no starting orientation is stored.
